  "brief": "Synchronization primitive that provides highly scalable concurrent read access to state which is infrequently updated. ",
  "category": "classes",
  "const": false,
  "definition": "",
  "details": "A [Toggle](/_autogen/Classes/classbatt_1_1Toggle/) maintains two copies of the protected state `T`: the active and the future. Readers have shared (const) access to the active state; Writers have exclusive access to the future state. When a Writer goes out of scope, releasing its exclusive lock on writing, it automatically installs the \"future\" instance of T as the new \"active;\" then it observes all reader's thread-local state. The next Writer must wait for any reader observed by the previous writer to leave its critical section at least once before continuing.\n\nT must be default-initializable. ",
  "explicit": false,
  "fullname": "batt::Toggle",
  "hasAdditionalMembers": true,
  "hasDetails": true,
  "includes": "<batteries/async/toggle.hpp>",
  "inline": false,
  "kind": "class",
